posts.name: Bibs
posts.description: A bib is a small piece of fabric that's tied under a baby's chin to keep food or milk from staining her clothes.

posts.name: Bodysuits
posts.description: A bodysuit is a one-piece form-fitting or skin-tight garment that covers the torso and the crotch, and sometimes the legs, hands, and feet, and cannot be used as a swimsuit.

posts.name: Mittens
posts.description: Mittens feature an elastic cuff to keep them securely on baby's hands.

posts.name: Cloth Diaper
posts.description: Usually made of absorbent cotton, bamboo, or hemp, fitted cloth baby diapers have a contour shape similar to a disposable diaper, with elastic or gathered edges at the legs and back to contain messes.
